# Next.js Patterns

## Server vs Client components

- Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when state, effects, or event handlers are needed
- Server pages fetch data and delegate rendering to a client component
- Page-specific client components live in `_components/` next to `page.tsx`
- Name pattern: `{PageName}PageContent.tsx`

## Server page pattern

```typescript
const Page = async () => {
  await requireLoggedIn();
  const supabase = await createClient();
  const [error, data] = await safeAwait(getData(supabase));
  if (error) return <ErrorAlert error={error} />;
  return <PageContent data={data} />;
};

export default Page;
```

## Co-located page files

- `page.callbacks.ts` — extracted event handlers and async logic, receiving dependencies (setState, dispatch, router) as parameters
- `page.constants.ts` — page-specific constants (step definitions, color maps, etc.)
- Pages import and wrap callbacks in `useCallback`, passing dependencies:

```typescript
const onAction = useCallback(
  (args) => handleAction(setError, dispatch, args),
  [dispatch],
);
```

## API routes

- Use `route.ts` with named exports matching HTTP methods (`POST`, `GET`, etc.)
- Accept `NextRequest`, return `NextResponse.json()` or `Response`
- Validate input at the top of the handler, return early on errors
- Keep heavy dependencies (Puppeteer, AI SDKs) lazy-loaded inside the handler

## Middleware

- Single root `src/middleware.ts` that delegates to `src/auth/auth.middleware.ts`
- Use `matcher` config to exclude static assets
- Auth middleware handles redirect logic (unauthenticated -> login, authenticated -> dashboard)

## Dynamic routes

- Folder convention: `[param]/` (e.g. `[id]/`)
- In Next.js 15+, `params` is a `Promise` that must be awaited:

```typescript
interface PageProps {
  readonly params: Promise<{ id: string }>;
}

const Page = async ({ params }: PageProps) => {
  const { id } = await params;
};
```

## Layout

- Root layout in `src/app/layout.tsx` wraps providers in order: MUI cache -> Redux store -> Theme -> Auth
- `export const metadata: Metadata` for static metadata in layouts and pages
- Use `generateMetadata` for dynamic per-route metadata when needed
